values:
So, I've been threshing wheat for the past couple of mornings.&nbsp;My coworker Danielle picks the heads of wheat, and I run 'em through the machine.&nbsp;This means that I don't have anything to do with the harvesting, and no control over it. I didn't tell Danielle how to do it, my supervisor did, and apparently he left out some rather important bits when he told her what to do.&nbsp;

Said supervisor came in this morning while I was threshing. He told me that we've pretty much ruined the experiment by dint of not&nbsp;harvesting out&nbsp;out each plant and doing their seeds individually. Would he tell Danielle this? No, he didn't want to do that.&nbsp;

End result: Minor experiment mucked up. Supervisor frustrated. I have been yelled at. Danielle is unaware that the problem ever existed.
